Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.28,0:00:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Dr. David Hawkins Sedona 2002\Nseries, The Way to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.03,0:00:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Lecture 4:\NPhosality and Duality.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.32,0:00:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Originally presented in April of 2002 at\Nthe Sedona Creative Life Center.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.71,0:00:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason we meet is uh to share what\Nwe've learned about uh our
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.60,0:00:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,investigations about the nature of\Nconsciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.32,0:00:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the only place I know of that is\Nactually doing
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.32,0:00:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual research.\NAs amazing as that may sound, there's
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.52,0:01:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,archaeologic research on religious\Nhistory.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.16,0:01:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And for that, you need a little pick and\Nand a pith hat and you go out in the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.72,0:01:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,desert and you hope to find something.\NBut that doesn't really advance human
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.60,0:01:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,knowledge, you see, really.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.15,0:01:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,what's unique about uh these talks is\Nthat we've um discovered a means of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.60,0:01:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,investigating\Nthe nonlinear domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.68,0:01:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We found a means of investigating that\Nwhich is unknowable by ordinary means.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.07,0:01:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And I share with you my own\Nexperiences as consciousness advance
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.40,0:01:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout this lifetime\Nand my own awareness of reality as I
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.07,0:01:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,experience it.\NSo it's both subjective and in terms of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.96,0:01:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the world objective and that we have\Num discovered a means of verifying truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.36,0:02:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,uh that's never been discovered before\Nwhich makes it very useful tool.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.36,0:02:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course everybody here is pretty\Naware that we discovered that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.03,0:02:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology itself made a very\Nuh incredible tool available to almost
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.00,0:02:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone if they calibrate over 200 and\Ntheir partner does and their question is
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.52,0:02:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,over 200 the results are valid.\Nuh we didn't even know that when we
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.31,0:02:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,wrote power versus force we said we\Nthought anybody could do it and then I
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.20,0:02:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,would get letters from people\Nuh that they were unable to make it work
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.31,0:02:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were trying to find out how to\Nget even with their mother-in-law make
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.44,0:02:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,money on the stock market and it could\Nbe the intention behind those things I
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.44,0:02:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,don't know but I began to suspect that\Nand then we discovered that um
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.72,0:02:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,if if the uh the question needs to be\Nintegris the intention
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.16,0:03:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,uh is what really sets the calibrable\Nlevel of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.31,0:03:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The the two people involved both need to\Nbe above 200. So it works therefore only
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.80,0:03:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,for about 15% of the population which I\Ndidn't know when I wrote power versus
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.51,0:03:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,force I think when I revised it for Hay\NHouse. So I did put that in there. The
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.87,0:03:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,caveat that uh\Nthe the purpose has to be integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.84,0:03:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The discovery was that chinesiology was\Nasking a question of the field of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.12,0:03:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness.\NConsciousness registers only that which
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.76,0:03:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is\Nconsequently
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.59,0:03:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the other error in power versus force is\NI said it was true versus false.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.72,0:03:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The correct the correct u explanation of\Nthe phenomena is it's either true or not
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.28,0:03:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,true.\NUh so because that which is real exists
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.31,0:04:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,then that which is real registers within\Nthe field of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.23,0:04:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is unreal, that which the\Nworld calls false has no independent
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.51,0:04:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,existence.\Ndoes not register in consciousness and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.04,0:04:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore gives you a weak response\Nand in terms of the world unknow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.23,0:04:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We said it's more analogous to\Nan electricity going down a wire. When
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.72,0:04:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,electricity is there, it's on. When\Nelectricity is off,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.91,0:04:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not on.\NBut there is no independent existent
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.96,0:04:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,thing such as offness.\NThat's an important point to get. There
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.19,0:04:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is no such thing as offness. And we'll\Nget to that more later in the lecture
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.84,0:04:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,because the lecture is supposed to be\Nabout
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.16,0:04:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,uh supposed to be about what's it about\Ntoday?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.19,0:05:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes. Well, anyway,\Nwhatever it's about, uh it's it's
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.24,0:05:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely important to realize this\Nessential truth
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.28,0:05:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is no such thing as offness.\NWe'll expand upon that later. Yes, today
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.12,0:05:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we're talking about positionality and uh\Nhow to transcend positionality because
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.80,0:05:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the undoing of the ego, the ego is based\Non
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.80,0:05:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,uh a whole series of positionalities of\Nincreasing elaboration.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.16,0:05:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll talk about the structure of the\Nego, its origin and how it expresses
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.36,0:05:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,itself in the human domain\Nand how to therefore to transcend it. A
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.28,0:05:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,great a great deal of information itself\Nis transformational.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.16,0:05:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,To merely hear certain things already\Nresolves the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.56,0:05:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not going to rain today. That takes\Ncare of that one right there. You see
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.60,0:06:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,what I'm saying?\NOne worry just got eliminated. You know
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.36,0:06:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,what I mean? So certain information\Nitself is transformational because it's
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.08,0:06:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so powerful. And if you calibrate the\Nlevel of certain pieces of information,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.44,0:06:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see why they are so powerful.\NEverything occurs uh we could start with
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.52,0:06:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a paradigm\Nof context and content. It's crucially
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.96,0:06:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,important to understand\Nthat what the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.36,0:06:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,experiences is content\Nand what enlightenment is concerned with
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.24,0:06:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is context.\Nthat God is the ultimate infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.28,0:06:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,context\Nand that all that all of existence is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.60,0:06:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,then content.\NAll that exists is content
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.80,0:06:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing comes into existence except\Nfor context.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.72,0:06:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, God is the source of all\Nexistence.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.75,0:07:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All that exists arises solely as a\Nspecific creation of God. You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.24,0:07:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we spoke about that when we were\Ndifferentiating uh evolution from
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.63,0:07:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,creation\Nthat contrary um to the ego's thought
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.96,0:07:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that causality works like a series of\Nbillyard balls. On the contrary, every
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.88,0:07:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,single moment because of creation, all\Nthat exists, its existence is because
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.91,0:07:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it is simultaneously and in every moment\Nbeing created by God. So God doesn't hit
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.12,0:07:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,ball A and then then go through all the\Nnext 14 balls until it comes out at the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.31,0:07:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,end, which is the traditional idea of\Nthe evolution of of evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.56,0:07:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,On the contrary, each and every movement\Nof each and every ball is an individual
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.52,0:08:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,creation of God. God creates this. God\Ncreates this. This God creates this. God
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.24,0:08:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,creates this. God creates this. So that\Nthe creator is continuously present. So
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.44,0:08:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that all that is happening is a\Ncontinuous creation which seems to be
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.36,0:08:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,sequential because it's perceived\Nsequentially.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.91,0:08:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But perception is not causality.\NSo to start out uh help you digest your
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.03,0:08:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,breakfast, I thought we'd start out with\Nthis
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.12,0:08:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,which will take us uh\Nuh from the Buddha nature right down to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.32,0:08:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,breakfast.\NI thought we'd start with an easy one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.36,0:08:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So we start with the simple awareness\Nthat the unmanifest is the godhead. In
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.16,0:08:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,other words, out of apparent\Nnothingness, the Buddha's void,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.83,0:09:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,um the Buddha nature, he has the\Nunmanifest having no form.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.16,0:09:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if the unmanifest is the\NBuddha nature. Yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.36,0:09:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,we have permission to ask this resist.\NThe unmanifest and the Buddha nature,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.51,0:09:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,one in the same resistance. Yeah. So\Nthis is what the Buddha is speaking of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.36,0:09:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,then\Nbecause in the enlightened state there
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.04,0:09:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is no form, there is no thingness,\Nthere is no positionality, there is no
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.16,0:09:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,time, space or any point of reference.\NSo it seems void. But the ultimate
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.16,0:09:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,reality is not nothingness.\NThe error which I spoke about previously
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.39,0:09:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and which I wrote about more extensively\Nin the book I'm finishing now
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.88,0:09:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is not to confuse the Buddha's void with\Nnothingness
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.32,0:09:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because as we said no there is no such\Nthing as offness neither can nothingness
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.12,0:10:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,exist\None branch of Buddhism leads you into
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.92,0:10:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the void and I've been there it's very\Nvery impressive
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.00,0:10:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is extremely impressive\Nand one is certain this is what the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.20,0:10:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha spoke of.\NHowever, it is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.95,0:10:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothingness cannot exist. And um any\Nmore than offness can exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.68,0:10:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Nif we have something here, we say
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.88,0:10:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,there's something here. If we take it\Naway, you have nothingness. But you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.04,0:10:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,can't give me a piece of nothingness\Nbecause it doesn't exist. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.64,0:10:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So the unmanifest then is that\Nwhich is prior you might say prior to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.20,0:10:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the universe which is just a way of\Nlanguaging it. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.04,0:10:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The next realization is that one is all\Nthat is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.60,0:11:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Um so I forget the calibrated levels of\Nthese. I think I've got it somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.68,0:11:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,else later this morning. Each one of\Nthese you can calibrate these levels of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.92,0:11:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness. This would be a thousand and\Nup manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.04,0:11:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As the ego disappears,\Nthere's like an agonizing shock, a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.68,0:11:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling of literally dying.\NPeople worry about physically dying. You
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.68,0:11:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,can forget about worrying about\Nphysically dying. There's nothing to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.80,0:11:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,physically dying. It's a snap. You're\Nout of the body. It's fantastic. You
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.56,0:11:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,wonder why you ever hung out with that\Nstupid thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.04,0:11:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't forget 99% of your fears and\Nworries have to do with the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.04,0:11:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,survival, money, health, uh,\Ntransportation, food, eating, breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.20,0:11:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, my god, it's a really drag. So,\Nthe minute you're out of it, you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.44,0:11:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh, this is fantastic." And then\Nsomebody shakes your knee and it's your
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.44,0:12:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,father and you can see he thinks you're\Nyou're dead. Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.64,0:12:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He believes in death. You see, he\Nbelieves in death. And if you don't go
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.24,0:12:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,back in the body and breathe again, he's\Ngoing to grieve.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.88,0:12:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if I'd been a true Buddha at that\Nm moment, I would have left it. It was
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.27,0:12:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,his problem.\NBut I wasn't a true Buddha. It was just
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.36,0:12:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,an enlightened state, but uh not the not\Nthe ultimate. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.20,0:12:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,one then reluctantly re-energizes the\Nbody, which is a terrible mistake, but
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.92,0:12:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway, you do it.\NThat was very codependent, right? We
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.80,0:12:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,call it codependent.\NYou agree to stay alive so your father
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.27,0:12:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,won't grieve over your death. I mean\Nthat's really neurotic, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.51,0:12:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's what happened. And more than\Nonce, more than once. All right. So
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.51,0:12:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in that state, in that state, one is all\Nthat is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.04,0:13:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the everythingness of allness.\NThis is self. The the awareness of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.12,0:13:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,reality as\Nas allness, the oneness and allness,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.16,0:13:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,complete totality,\Ninfinitude beyond beginnings or endings.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.16,0:13:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that state, one knows that that\Nwhich I am has always existed before
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.36,0:13:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,this universe, before other universes,\Nwhen all universes have come and gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.27,0:13:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that which I am\Num is continuous because one that's
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.88,0:13:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencing God as allness.\NThe state prior to that is the awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.92,0:13:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that the these are states you can reach\Nthrough meditation and we'll get into
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.16,0:13:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that in in another lecture.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.16,0:13:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,when you when you when you you in\Nmeditation get to identify with the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.56,0:13:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,observer witness rather than the content\Nof consciousness. I should have started
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.56,0:14:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from the other end.\NWe should start with the dog here. The
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.32,0:14:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,dog is barking and my leg is hurting and\Nmy name is George
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.04,0:14:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and you are stuck with form.\NAs you begin to meditate, you see that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.63,0:14:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,all this is going through your mind and\Nyou say this is hopeless. I cannot stop
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.04,0:14:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind. It's uh relentless. It's\Nthinking all the time, feeling all the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.76,0:14:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,time, imagining things, remembering\Nthings. It's a cacony. It just goes on
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.95,0:14:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and on. So at this point, the ordinary\Nperson as they walk around in the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.51,0:14:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,universe, 99.9% of people identify with\Nform and that's why they're so
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.12,0:14:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,preoccupied with health and wealth and\Ndeath and all that kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.12,0:14:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh because they are form and they\Nidentify life as form
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.60,0:14:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is I am the body and I am the\Ncontent of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.36,0:14:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The person as they start to get involved\Nin spiritual work begins to realize that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.60,0:15:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a step beyond that that the mind\Nis somehow registering somewhere. I say
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.16,0:15:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to people say I can't stop my mind. I\Ncan't do this and that. I say well how
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.04,0:15:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,do you know what your mind is doing?\NYou're complaining. What are you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.00,0:15:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,complaining about?\NWell, you must be aware of what the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.24,0:15:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is doing. So it's registering somewhere.\NSo this begins to pull you back from the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.48,0:15:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,identification with content and you see\Nthat something is registering what's
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.68,0:15:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,going on in the mind\Nand that something is recognizing the
