Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.88,0:16:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,are impersonal. You realize that\Nobserving and witnessing are happening
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.19,0:16:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of their own. There is no you that is\Nwatching and witnessing. Although in the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.83,0:16:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning you have the illusion that's\Nyou that's watching and observing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.83,0:16:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Except that you then begin to notice it\Ndoes it all the time without being
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.19,0:16:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,asked. So if it was you, you could\Ncontrol it. You could stop witnessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.07,0:16:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You could stop watching. You could stop\Nobserving. But you begin to realize that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.19,0:16:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,this is happening of its own and you\Ndisidentify that with it with with that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.88,0:16:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see that that is coming out of\Nconsciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.12,0:17:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you as you see you progressively\Nlet go identifying with content and you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.16,0:17:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,progressively expanding and identifying\Nwith context.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.12,0:17:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is very very limited. This is\Nvery specific, very restricting
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.79,0:17:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is completely content when\Nyou're just you're ignoring the con
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.24,0:17:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,context altogether. Here you're ignoring\Ncontext.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.40,0:17:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,As you move up, you begin to relinquish\Nyour identification with content and you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.08,0:17:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,begin to realize that that which you are\Nis context. It is because of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.79,0:17:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness that any of the lower\Nstates can occur in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.67,0:17:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason you realize they're not you\Nis because you have no control of them
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.67,0:17:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see they're happening\Nspontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.79,0:17:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness is there in and of itself\Nwithout being asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.32,0:17:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You can become unconscious of\Nconsciousness when you go to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.36,0:18:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the oblivion.\NThat's not the void. That's oblivion.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.91,0:18:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And many people like oblivion.\NAnd why do they like oblivion?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.24,0:18:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's so peaceful and happy. How\Ndo you know it's peaceful and happy? So
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.67,0:18:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you weren't oblivious. You were aware\Nthat it was peaceful and happy. And you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.79,0:18:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,said it to everybody how well you slept\Nlast night. So something is aware
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.84,0:18:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway. And so\Nwe move up these levels
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.91,0:18:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and realize that that's where we are at\Nthe top.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.00,0:18:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody realizes now that you're the\Nunmanifest, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.52,0:18:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted to demonstrate for the\Ndoubting Thomas' here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.12,0:18:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand up. Ding Thomas', where are you?\NLet me just ask if we can do this.
