Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.91,0:22:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Middle East is over 60. 65.\NJeez, it was 70. It's gone down.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.79,0:22:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask about Mr. Bin\NLowden. Resist. He's over 65. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.08,0:22:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No. So, you see\Nthe Let's do the dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.32,0:22:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The dinosaurs are over 30, 35, 40, 45,\N50, 55, 60, 65.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.12,0:22:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm. Very interesting, isn't it?\NSo, we see the evolution of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.55,0:22:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll have to in in the book I I'm\Nfinishing up trying to track the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.36,0:23:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution of consciousness as it\Nappeared on the planet and then evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.20,0:23:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout time\Non up to the present day.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.88,0:23:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to recapitulate\Nlife and all of its expressions,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.00,0:23:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,especially as consciousness and as all\Nof life throughout all of time as it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.32,0:23:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,evolved on this planet. I thought I'd do\Nthat before lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.03,0:23:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes me warm just to think of it. So\Nanyway, that's what we're doing. And uh
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.28,0:23:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but you see that life then appeared.\NWhat happened to our diagram? Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.32,0:23:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway, it\Nit appeared out of the unmanifest
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.08,0:23:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming manifest and the light of\Nconsciousness then shone forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.84,0:23:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, and creation arose out of the man\Nunmanifest as the manifest. So God as
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.84,0:24:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,unmanifest is infinite potentiality.\N>> That's the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.15,0:24:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, so this is infinite potentiality.\NInfinite potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.27,0:24:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the infinite context\Nof all of creation is unmanifest. The
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.44,0:24:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,context\Nis infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.72,0:24:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity of the unmanifest is beyond\Nman's imagination. And no writer has
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.91,0:24:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,really touched\Nhas really gotten what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.12,0:24:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The\Nunmanifest
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.72,0:24:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,has the capacity for creativity. It's\Ninnate to its nature
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.27,0:24:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that it creates has within it\Nthe nature of that which created it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.79,0:25:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So that\Ncreation
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.24,0:25:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is continuous and infinite.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.88,0:25:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we tend to think of the creator as\Ncreating this world. More sophisticated
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.79,0:25:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,person thinks of the creator as creating\Nour universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.84,0:25:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite universe.\NBut beyond this universe is an infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.48,0:25:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,universe of universes,\Neach of which is at faster than the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.15,0:25:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,speed of light, creating an infinite\Nseries of universes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.67,0:25:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Is that so?\NThat's not resistant. That is so
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.00,0:25:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,resistant.\NOut of an infinite series of infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.96,0:25:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,universes\Nare arising simultaneously faster than
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.44,0:25:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the speed of light.\NInfinite universes continuously.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.55,0:26:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, that sort of expands\None's concept of the creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.72,0:26:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing comes into existence without\Nhaving come from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.24,0:26:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing within the physical domain\Nhas within it power. It has within
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.79,0:26:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,itself\Nonly that expression in form that we
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.44,0:26:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,call force.\NNothing that exists has the power to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.36,0:26:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,create its own existence.\NNothing that exists has within it the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.91,0:26:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,power to create its own existence.\NAll that exists arises from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.00,0:26:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo this
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.20,0:27:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the unmanifest arises the light,\Nthe light of consciousness where this
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.00,0:27:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite power\Ninteracting with matter
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.96,0:27:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have life united with matter.\NAnd creation as we know it then is the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.27,0:27:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,lighting of matter by the light of\Nconsciousness as life. The life then
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.72,0:27:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,evolved on this planet through very\Nrudimentary forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.84,0:27:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It did not occur spontaneously as a\Nhappy accidental combination of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.08,0:27:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,chemicals as\Nuh sort of pedestrian science would have
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.72,0:27:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you think. Don't forget science is on\Ndifferent levels too. And what people
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.96,0:27:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,think of as science varies all the way\Nfrom the somewhat stupid to the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.40,0:27:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,brilliant.\NJust because it's labeled science
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.08,0:27:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't think it mean that it's highly\Nintelligent. Very often it isn't. And uh
