Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.44,0:28:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway according to that theory of\Nevolution then there was a happy
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.67,0:28:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,combination of chemicals that began to\Nbreathe and think which is you know
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.03,0:28:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,unlikely.\NWhy is it unlikely? because you're
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.55,0:28:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,mixing categories. There are two two\Ndifferent categories of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.36,0:28:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Materiality has no capacity for\Nconsciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.91,0:28:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very obvious to to anybody that\Nthinks about it. That for anything to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.79,0:28:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,evolve has to have a pattern. And where\Nwould this pattern arise? Well, the
